from sklearn.decomposition import PCA
from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import numpy as np

# Standardize the data (mean=0, std=1)
scaler = StandardScaler()
standardized_data = scaler.fit_transform(pivoted_df_2)

# Perform PCA with defined number of components which is 3
num_components =  3
pca = PCA(n_components=num_components)
principal_components = pca.fit_transform(standardized_data)

# Explained variance ratio
explained_variance_ratio = pca.explained_variance_ratio_
cumulative_variance = np.cumsum(explained_variance_ratio)
print("Explained Variance Ratio:", explained_variance_ratio)
print("Explained Cumulative Variance Ratio:", cumulative_variance)

# Get the loadings
loadings = pca.components_
print("Loadings:",loadings)
plt.figure(figsize=(15, 5))
plt.subplot(1, 2, 1)
plt.plot(range(1, num_components + 1), explained_variance_ratio, marker='o')
plt.xlabel("Number of Principal Components")
plt.ylabel("Variance Explained")
plt.title("Variance Explained by Principal Components")

plt.subplot(1, 2, 2)
plt.bar(range(1, len(cumulative_variance) + 1), cumulative_variance, align='center', alpha=0.5)
plt.xlabel("Number of Principal Components")
plt.ylabel("Cumulative Variance Explained")
plt.title("Cumulative Variance Explained by Principal Components")

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()
